tic neoplasm covered by a thin clear membrane.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2016150212&amp;id=fig16c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Wippold FJ 2nd, Lubner M, Perrin RJ, Lämmle M, Perry A. Neuropathology for the neuroradiologist: Antoni A and Antoni B tissue patterns. <em>AJNR Am J Neuroradiol</em> 2007;28(9):1633–1638.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.3174/ajnr.A0682">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17893219/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Neuropathology+for+the+neuroradiologist%3A+Antoni+A+and+Antoni+B+tissue+patterns&amp;author=FJ+Wippold&amp;author=M+Lubner&amp;author=RJ+Perrin&amp;author=M+L%C3%A4mmle&amp;author=A+Perry&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=AJNR+Am+J+Neuroradiol&amp;pages=1633-1638&amp;doi=10.3174%2Fajnr.A0682&amp;pmid=17893219">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Delgado J, Jaramillo D, Ho-Fung V, Fisher MJ, Anupindi SA. MRI features of plexiform neurofibromas involving the liver and pancreas in children with neurofibromatosis type 1. <em>Clin Radiol</em> 2014;69(6):e280–e284.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.crad.2014.01.020">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24594377/">PubMed</a></div><div 